    public abstract class AbstractPetriNet<P extends AbstractPlace<F,S>,T extends AbstractTransition<F,S>,F extends AbstractFlowRelation<P,T,S>,M extends AbstractMarking<S>,S>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TransitionListener<AbstractTransition<F,S>>, TokenListener<AbstractPlace<F,S>>, de.uni.freiburg.iig.telematik.jagal.traverse.Traversable<AbstractPNNode<F>>, FlowRelationListener<AbstractFlowRelation<P,T,S>>, PlaceListener<AbstractPlace<F,S>>, PNStructureListener<P,T,F,M,S>, PNMarkingListener<S,M>, java.io.Serializable, de.invation.code.toval.misc.NamedComponent
    Abstract class for defining Petri nets and their properties.

    It contains major properties like the places, transitions and relations of a Petri net and provides methods for adding/removing them.

    It keeps track of the nets' state by remembering the marking of the net which describes the number and kind of tokens contained in net places. The net state changes when transitions fire. Using listeners, the net reacts on changes of transitions and places that belong to the net.
    It also keeps track of enabled transitions, transition and place sources/drains. A transition is enabled if all its precondition hold.
    Preconditions are defined in the sense of constraints on the number and kind
    of tokens contained in places that have outgoing relations to the transition.
    In case an enabled transition fires, it removes tokens from incoming places and puts tokens into outgoing places.
    This class allows to fire an enabled transition.
    In case there is more than one transition, the FlowControl determines the transition to fire.
    作者:
    Thomas Stocker

      • addTransitions

        public final boolean addTransitions(java.util.Collection<java.lang.String> transitionNames)
        Adds transitions with the given names to the Petri net.
        Transitions names have to be unique. In case the net already contains transitions with given names, less transitions than the given number of arguments may be added to the Petri net.
        This method calls addTransition(String) for each transition name.
        参数:
        transitionNames - Names for the Petri net transitions.
        返回:
        true if at least one transition was successfully added;
        false otherwise.
        抛出:
        de.invation.code.toval.validate.ParameterException - If the set of transition names is null or some transition names are null.
        另请参阅:
        addTransition(String)

        Place names have to be unique. In case the net already contains places with given names, less places than the given number of arguments may be added to the Petri net.
        This method calls addPlace(String) for each place name.
        参数:
        placeNames - Names for the Petri net places to add.
        notifyListeners - Set true if listeners should be notified.
        返回:
        true if at least one place was successfully added;
        false otherwise.
        抛出:
        de.invation.code.toval.validate.ParameterException - If the set of place names is null or some place names are null.
        另请参阅:
        addPlace(String)

        Warning: This non-final method gets called by constructors.
        返回:

      • setInitialMarking

        public void setInitialMarking(M marking)
        Sets the initial marking of the Petri net.
        The initial marking defines the initial state of a Petri net in the sense of tokens contained in places. When a Petri net is reset (reset()), it should reach its initial marking.
        The initial marking does not have to contain all net places. For places not contained in the given initial marking, the net assumes 0 tokens in the initial net state.
        This method uses setInitialMarking(AbstractMarking) to actually transform the net state to the initial state.
        参数:
        marking - The marking used as initial marking (state) of the net.

      • getInitialMarking

        public M getInitialMarking()
        Returns the initial marking of the Petri net.
        The initial marking defines the initial state of a Petri net in the sense of tokens contained in places.
        返回:
        The initial marking of the net.

      • setMarking

        public void setMarking(M marking)
        Sets the marking of the Petri net.
        The net marking defines states for Petri net classes.
        In case the given marking does not define a state for a net place,
        its state is set to empty, i.e. all tokens are removed.
        参数:
        marking - The desired net marking.
